burnPosition(uint256).details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params.tokenId: The ID of the LP position to be burned.

decreaseLiquidity(uint256,uint128,addres.details: Only the Borrower Operations contract can call this function.

params._liquidityToRemove: The amount of liquidity to be removed from the LP position.
params._tokenId: The ID of the LP position to be decreased.

returns.amount0: The amount of token0 removed from the LP position.
returns.amount1: The amount of token1 removed from the LP position.

decreaseMintedSupply(uint256,address).details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params._amount: The amount of minted supply to be removed from the protocol.

returns.amount0: The amount of token0 owed to the position.
returns.amount1: The amount of token1 owed to the position.

returns.sum: The total amount of ETH collateral in the Active Pool.

returns._0: MAX_SUPPLY The maximum amount of GHO the protocol can mint.
mintedSupply The total amount of GHO minted by the protocol.

increaseLiquidity(address,uint256,uint25.details: Only the Borrower Operations contract can call this function.

params._tokenId: The ID of the LP position to be increased.
params.amountAdd0: The amount of token0 to be added to the LP position.
params.amountAdd1: The amount of token1 to be added to the LP position.
params.sender: The address of the account that is increasing the liquidity of the LP position.

returns.amount0: The amount of token0 added to the LP position.
returns.amount1: The amount of token1 added to the LP position.
returns.liquidity: The amount of liquidity added to the LP position.

increaseMintedSupply(uint256,address,uin.details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params._amount: The amount of minted supply to be added to the protocol.

mintPosition((address,address,uint24,int.details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params.params: The parameters for the LP position to be minted.

returns.tokenId: The ID of the newly minted LP position.

returns._0: selector The Selector of the IERC721Receiver interface.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

repayInterestFromUserToProtocol(address,.details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params.amount: The amount of interest to be repaid.
params.sender: The address of the user that will repay the interest.

sendPosition(address,uint256).details: Only the Borrower Operations contract or the LP Positions Manager contract can call this function.

params._account: The address of the account that will receive the LP Position.
params._tokenId: The ID of the LP Position to be sent.

setAddresses(address,address).details: The function also sets the lpPositionsManager variable to the LP Positions Manager contract and emits an event to notify of the change in the Borrower Operations address.Only the contract owner can call this function.

params._borrowerOperationsAddress: The address of the Borrower Operations contract.
params._lpPositionsManagerAddress: The address of the LP Positions Manager contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

decreaseLiquidity(uint256,uint128,addres.notice: Decreases the liquidity of an LP position.

feesOwed((uint256,address,uint128,uint12.notice: Returns the total amount of tokens owed to a position.

getCollateralValue().notice: Returns the total amount of ETH collateral in the Active Pool.

getMaxSupply().notice: Returns the maximum amount of GHO the protocol can mint.

getMintedSupply().notice: Returns the total amount of GHO minted by the protocol.

increaseLiquidity(address,uint256,uint25.notice: Increases the liquidity of an LP position.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Returns the address of the contract that implements the IERC721Receiver interface.

repayInterestFromUserToProtocol(address,.notice: Repays the interest of a user.

sendPosition(address,uint256).notice: Sends an LP Position to an account.

setAddresses(address,address).notice: Sets the addresses for the Borrower Operations and LP Positions Manager contracts.
